# .dockerignore — root build context exclusions for the SMS Platform monorepo.
# Closes Pitfall 8 (BLOCKER for GA): .env / secrets / planning state must NEVER
# enter a docker build context, because COPY . . layers are visible via
# `docker history` and trivially extractable from any pulled image.
#
# Phase 24 lands this baseline. Phase 25 may add per-app `.dockerignore` files
# under apps/api/ and apps/web/ — Docker BuildKit applies the closest
# `.dockerignore` to each build context, so this file remains the project-wide
# default for any root-level `docker build`.
#
# Pattern ordering note: the negation pattern `!.env.example` MUST appear AFTER
# `.env*` because BuildKit applies rules in order. Reordering the Secrets group
# below would silently re-leak the real .env file.

# === Secrets (HIGHEST PRIORITY — BLOCKER for GA) ===
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# === Version control ===
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# === Dependencies ===
node_modules
**/node_modules

# === Build artifacts ===
dist
**/dist
.next
**/.next
out
**/out
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# === Test / coverage ===
coverage
**/coverage

# === Planning / GSD state ===
.planning
apps/*/.planning

# === Local bind-mounted data (dev compose HLS bind mount, snapshots, etc.) ===
docker-data

# === IDE / editor ===
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo

# === OS metadata ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# === Claude / agent state ===
.claude

# === Logs ===
*.log
**/*.log

# === Local bulk-import examples (may contain real customer URLs / creds) ===
bulk-import-*-EXAMPLE.csv
bulk-import-*-EXAMPLE.xlsx
